00:14:07.077 --> 00:14:08.805
"anybody else, you have a style."

339
00:14:08.805 --> 00:14:11.311
And I kind of go more into that.

340
00:14:11.311 --> 00:14:15.908
Realizing that whether you're creating some...

341
00:14:17.768 --> 00:14:19.944
Let's say artistic thing through an artistic

342
00:14:19.944 --> 00:14:22.450
vehicle in a very specific kind of constricted way.

343
00:14:22.450 --> 00:14:24.722
Like it's a symphony or a poem or this or that or painting.

344
00:14:24.722 --> 00:14:27.900
You know why is that considered art and someone

345
00:14:27.900 --> 00:14:31.388
whose had recipes handed down for generations

346
00:14:31.388 --> 00:14:34.055
or puts their own twist on it and makes a table full

347
00:14:34.055 --> 00:14:36.497
of people happy every night, why isn't that creative?

348
00:14:36.497 --> 00:14:38.830
I think that's beautiful, and I think that's very creative.

349
00:14:39.660 --> 00:14:43.420
So part of it is, for me, opening up the definition

350
00:14:43.420 --> 00:14:47.943
of creativity to say that we are all creative

351
00:14:47.943 --> 00:14:50.780
because we are constantly being created.

352
00:14:52.090 --> 00:14:53.735
And it's just the nature of the universe.

353
00:14:53.735 --> 00:14:57.425
What is creativity? It is life happening.

354
00:14:57.425 --> 00:14:59.675
<v Voiceover>Anything you can conceive of, really.</v>

355
00:14:59.675 --> 00:15:02.342
<v ->It's not even what I can conceive of, it's happening</v>

356
00:15:02.342 --> 00:15:03.569
in spite of what I can conceive of.

357
00:15:03.569 --> 00:15:06.086
It is the life force of all the universe just happening.

358
00:15:06.086 --> 00:15:07.312
It's creation all the time.

359
00:15:07.312 --> 00:15:08.454
<v Voiceover>That's true.</v>

360
00:15:08.454 --> 00:15:10.288
<v ->So in that we are in body, in that we have been</v>

361
00:15:10.288 --> 00:15:14.747
privileged to be in existence, okay.

362
00:15:14.747 --> 00:15:16.208
Cause I think being here is a privilege.

363
00:15:16.208 --> 00:15:20.250
We are constantly creative because we are being

364
00:15:20.250 --> 00:15:22.063
creative in spite of ourselves.

365
00:15:22.063 --> 00:15:24.005
Even if someone says, "I'm not creative,"

366
00:15:24.005 --> 00:15:26.746
that's pretty creative, that whole act

